## 6-Month Pre-Mortem
<!--
Pre-mortem methodology (Gary Klein, HBR 2007). Prospective hindsight — imagining
the failure has ALREADY happened — increases the ability to correctly identify
failure causes by ~30% vs. ordinary forward-looking risk analysis.

Process:
  1. Picture today + 6 months. The initiative has FAILED catastrophically.
     Look back from that future point.
  2. Write at least 5 distinct failure modes silently and individually
     (if multiple people, share only after writing — avoid groupthink).
  3. For each failure mode, score Likelihood (H/M/L) × Impact (H/M/L) and
     pair it with a mitigation that can be STARTED THIS WEEK.
  4. Re-run this section every 3–4 months to surface emerging risks.

Persona: founder + pm (use defer-to-persona if asked of a programmer/architect).
-->

### Failure modes (rank by likelihood × impact, top 5+)

