## Cash Flow Planning — 5 Scenarios (18-month horizon)
<!--
Industry practice (Abacum 2025): startups that prepare 3+ scenarios secure 1.8×
the funding of those relying on a single projection. We use 5 (the three middle
scenarios must each be PLAUSIBLE — defensible numbers, not aspirations):

  Worst         — multiple bad assumptions break at once
  Conservative  — realistic downside; one or two soft spots
  Base          — current trajectory, no surprises
  Optimistic    — realistic upside; two or three things go right
  Exceptional   — best-defensible-case, not fantasy

Stress-test deltas (per scenario, vs. base):
                       Worst    Conservative   Base   Optimistic   Exceptional
  Revenue growth       -50%     -20%           0      +25%         +60%
  CAC                  +75%     +25%           0      -15%         -30%
  Monthly churn        2.0×     1.3×           1.0×   0.8×         0.6×
  Time-to-first-pay    +60d     +30d           normal -15d         -30d

SaaS cash timing notes:
  - Prepaid annual plans bring cash in upfront — large positive cash impact
    that doesn't match GAAP revenue recognition.
  - Monthly plans match recognition more closely but smooth slower.
  - Track cash IN, not just amount: payment behavior matters.
  - Separate fixed burn (salaries, rent — slow to cut) from variable
    (marketing, hiring pace — fast to cut).

Persona: founder + technical-founder. Defer to founder if asked of others.
-->

